description:
&lt;p&gt;Midlands Medical Partnership ( MMP) is a group partnership which provides NHS GP services to over 65,000 patients over 10 surgeries across Birmingham, with 16 GP Partners and 20 Practice Nurses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experienced Practice Nurses required.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work pattern: Monday / Tuesday / Wednesday/ Thursday / Friday - hours to be discussed.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic &amp; highly motivated Practice Nurses to join our friendly practice team providing high quality care to our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working alongside a Senior Practice Nurse and an HCA, as well as GPs, reception and administration support staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MMP has a very supportive Practice Nurse network across all our sites with regular nurse meetings and an active in-house education programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking to recruit the right individuals with at least one year&#39;s experience in general practice&lt;/strong&gt;. Someone who is confident in working independently yet is able to work collaboratively with other members of the primary care team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should have experience of carrying out the full range of practice nurse duties, including childhood immunisations &amp; cervical screening &amp; will be expected to work to templates to ensure that the practice retains high achievement in QOF &amp; Enhanced services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Professional development is actively encouraged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We offer a structured salary based upon clinical activities.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please ensure you complete the application form in full. Partially completed forms will not be accepted.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
